# Project Standards and Architecture

Follow these instructions strictly for any code generation, refactoring, or editing.

## Tech Stack
- Framework: React
- Build Tool: Vite
- Package Manager: pnpm
- Language: TypeScript
- UI Library: Ant Design (Antd)

## Component Folder Structure
Every component must be placed in its own folder named after the component. 
The folder must contain:
- `index.tsx`: The main component logic and UI.
- `styles.module.css`: Use CSS Modules for styling.
- `consts.ts`: For component-specific constants (if needed).
- `utils.ts`: For component-specific helper functions (if needed).

## Styling and Quality Rules
- Strictly NO inline styles. Use CSS Modules.
- Use Strict TypeScript. Do not use `any`.
- Do not use `eslint-disable` or `@ts-ignore` comments.
- Prioritize Ant Design (Antd) components for the UI.
- Make all layouts responsive. 
- Always include loading states and error handling for API requests.
- All code, variable names, and comments must be in English.